International Automobile Federation (FIA) president Jean Todt is the latest recipient of the coveted First Class Chief of the Order of the Burning Spear (CBS) honour. Todt was feted on Saturday evening in recognition of his distinguished and outstanding service rendered to Kenya and the world in motorsports. Head of Public Service Dr Joseph Kinyua presented the award on behalf of His Excellency the President Uhuru Kenyatta at a ceremony graced by Cabinet Secretary for Sports, Culture and Heritage Amb. Amina Mohamed. The FIA President is among the motorsports crème de la crème who arrived in the country to celebrate the ongoing WRC Safari Rally which made a grand return to the FIA WRC calendar for the first time since 2002. The accolade is among the orders, decorations, and medals of Kenya awarded by the President of Kenya to distinguished services rendered to the nation in various capacities and responsibilities. The beneficiaries are recommended to the president by the National Honours and Awards Committee in the president's office. The Chief of the Order of the Golden Heart is the highest honour awarded by the Kenyan government.